# Lease Review Checklist

## Before Signing Any Lease Agreement

### Parties & Property Information
☐ All parties identified correctly (full legal names)
☐ Property address is accurate and complete
☐ Property description includes unit number, parking spaces, storage
☐ All signatures required are present
☐ Dates are filled in correctly

### Financial Terms
☐ Rent amount is clearly stated
☐ Due date specified (e.g., 1st of each month)
☐ Payment method explained (check, ACH, online portal)
☐ Late fees are specified and within state limits
☐ Security deposit amount stated
☐ Security deposit return terms included (timeline, deductions)
☐ First month's rent and deposit amounts match agreement
☐ Any additional fees disclosed (pet fees, parking, utilities)

### Lease Term & Duration
☐ Start date and end date clearly specified
☐ Lease term length is correct (e.g., 12 months)
☐ Renewal terms explained
☐ Notice period for termination/non-renewal specified
☐ Month-to-month terms (if applicable)

### Maintenance & Repairs
☐ Landlord maintenance responsibilities listed
☐ Tenant maintenance responsibilities listed
☐ Emergency repair procedures outlined
☐ Response timeline for repairs specified
☐ HVAC, plumbing, appliance maintenance covered

### Rules & Restrictions
☐ Pet policy clearly stated (if pets allowed)
☐ Smoking policy specified
☐ Noise restrictions outlined
☐ Guest/occupancy limits explained
☐ Subletting rules included
☐ Alteration/modification restrictions

### Legal Disclosures (State-Specific)
☐ Lead-based paint disclosure (pre-1978 buildings)
☐ Mold disclosure
☐ Pest control notice
☐ Bedbug disclosure
☐ Sex offender database notice
☐ Flood zone disclosure (if applicable)
☐ HOA rules provided (if applicable)

### Entry & Privacy
☐ Landlord entry notice requirements (typically 24-48 hours)
☐ Permitted reasons for entry listed
☐ Emergency entry provisions
☐ Inspection schedules disclosed

### Utilities & Services
☐ Utilities responsibility assigned (landlord vs. tenant)
☐ Trash collection explained
☐ Internet/cable responsibility
☐ Lawn care/snow removal assigned
☐ Common area maintenance explained

### Termination Clauses
☐ Early termination provisions included
☐ Break lease penalties specified
☐ Eviction procedures outlined
☐ Default consequences explained
☐ Military clause (SCRA) included

### Insurance & Liability
☐ Renter's insurance requirement stated
☐ Landlord's insurance responsibilities
☐ Liability for damages explained
☐ Personal property coverage addressed

### Special Provisions
☐ Parking space assigned
☐ Storage space designated
☐ Access codes/keys explained
☐ Move-in inspection scheduled
☐ Inventory of furnishings (if furnished)

## Red Flags to Watch For

⚠️ Automatic renewal without notice requirement
⚠️ Excessive late fees (check your state's limits)
⚠️ Landlord can enter "anytime" (violates privacy laws)
⚠️ Waiver of landlord liability for injuries
⚠️ Tenant pays for all repairs including structural
⚠️ No right to repair and deduct
⚠️ Liquidated damages clauses
⚠️ Attorney fees favor only landlord (must be mutual)
⚠️ Incomplete property description
⚠️ Missing required state disclosures
⚠️ Unclear rent increase procedures
⚠️ No itemization requirement for deposit deductions
⚠️ Shorter return period than state requires

## State-Specific Verification

### California
☐ Security deposit ≤ 1 month's rent (as of 2024, AB 12)
☐ 21-day deposit return timeline
☐ AB 1482 rent control compliance (5% + CPI, max 10%)
☐ Just cause eviction provisions
☐ All required disclosures included

### Texas
☐ Security deposit terms reasonable
☐ 30-day deposit return timeline
☐ Property condition form provided

### Florida
☐ Security deposit return timeline: 15-60 days
☐ Radon disclosure included
☐ Interest on deposits (if applicable)

### New York
☐ Security deposit ≤ 1 month's rent
☐ 14-day deposit return timeline
☐ Rent stabilization disclosure (if applicable)

### Illinois
☐ 30-45 day deposit return (varies by location)
☐ Interest on deposits if held 6+ months
☐ Chicago-specific ordinances (if applicable)

## After Review

☐ Keep a copy of the signed lease
☐ Document property condition with photos/video
☐ Get receipt for deposit payment
☐ Request move-in inspection report
☐ Set calendar reminders for:
  - Rent due dates
  - Lease renewal deadlines
  - Inspection dates
  - Rent increase notice periods

## Pro Tips

1. **Read Everything**: Don't skip the fine print or attachments
2. **Ask Questions**: If anything is unclear, ask for clarification
3. **Get It In Writing**: Verbal agreements don't count
4. **Use AI Tools**: LeaseLenses can analyze your lease in 5 minutes
5. **Consult an Attorney**: For complex situations or large amounts
6. **Compare to Standards**: Check if terms match state laws
7. **Document Everything**: Photos, emails, receipts
8. **Know Your Rights**: Research your state's landlord-tenant laws

